Home / About Us / Our Companies












By Name
By Segment





B


Behr Process Corporation





Behr Process Corporation




	Headquartered in Santa Ana, California, Behr Process Corporation is one of the largest suppliers of architectural paint and exterior wood care products to the United States and Canadian do-it-yourself markets.  Behr manufactures paints, decorative finishes, primers, stains and surface preparation products, which are sold exclusively at The Home Depot.  With a complete line of interior and exterior paints plus stains and specialty coatings, Behr Process offers a product for virtually every consumer coating need.

Visit Site
 






BrassCraft Manufacturing





BrassCraft Manufacturing




	BrassCraft Manufacturing markets high-quality gas connectors, appliance connectors, water connectors and water stops designed, assembled and machined in the United States.  A broad distribution model integrates a wide array of channel partners in the United States, Canada and Mexico which includes wholesalers, retailers and special markets.  These channel partners primarily serve the repair and remodel segments for residential and commercial markets.  Along with Cobra® drain cleaning products and BrassCraft® service parts, the BrassCraft has set the plumbing standard for over 65 years.

Visit Site
 






Brasstech





Brasstech




	Located in Santa Ana, California, Brasstech is a leading manufacturer in the premium and luxury kitchen and bath faucets, accessories, and lighting for the residential and hospitality markets. Brasstech products are distributed throughout the United States via specialty kitchen and bath showrooms and wholesalers. Brasstech manufactures and markets products in traditional, transitional and contemporary design styles under brands such as Newport Brass and Ginger.

Visit Site
 






Bristan Group





Bristan Group




	Bristan Group is the UK’s leading supplier of bathroom products including bathroom, kitchen and shower faucets, shower enclosures, sanitaryware, decorative heating and bathroom accessories.  Bristan’s foundation has been built on its belief that offering reliable, efficient and friendly customer service is every bit as important as offering a comprehensive range of quality products.  Its head office is in Tamworth, Staffordshire, where a state-of-the=art’ distribution center helps the Group maintain its industry-leading next day delivery service.

Visit Site
 







D


Delta Faucet Company





Delta Faucet Company




	Founded by Masco Corporation in 1954, Delta Faucet Company is a worldwide leader in faucets, flush valves and related accessories. The company manufactures Delta®, Brizo® and Peerless® branded products. Combining style and innovation, Delta Faucet Company’s extensive product line suits both residential and commercial buildings, including the urban-loft, high-rise, hospitality and long-term care sectors. With a wide array of intuitive electronic products, as well as technologies that improve the user experience and provide installation enhancements, Delta Faucet Company is America’s Faucet Innovation Leader.
	 

	As a company that delivers water every day through millions of faucets worldwide, Delta Faucet Company places a high priority on products that address today’s environmental concerns, such as water conservation and water quality. The company was named the 2011 WaterSense® Manufacturer Partner of the Year by the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency in recognition of its commitment to developing innovative products that promote water efficiency without compromising the user’s experience.

Visit Site
 







H


Hansgrohe SE





Hansgrohe SE




	The Hansgrohe Group is based in Schiltach, in Germany’s Black Forest. In its 115-year history, it has acquired a reputation as a leading innovator in technology, design and sustainability in the sanitation industry. The mixers, showerheads and shower systems created by the Hansgrohe Group are original products that make bathrooms more functional, more comfortable and more aesthetically pleasing. The quality products of the company’s brands Axor and Hansgrohe can be found in such prestigious venues as the luxury ocean liner Queen Mary II, London Heathrow Airport Terminal 5, the Burj Khalifa in Dubai (the world’s tallest building), the German Chancellery in Berlin, New York’s Yoo luxury residences and the Masdar City Institute of Science and Technology in Abu Dhabi. The company and its products have been honoured with numerous awards, most recently the iF Award Gold 2015. The Hansgrohe Group ranks in 10th position among 2,000 companies listed in the iF World Design Guide Company Ranking. With production sites in Germany, France, the Netherlands, the USA and China, 34 companies and 21 sales offices across the globe, and products supplied in 143 countries, the Hansgrohe Group has a worldwide presence in the sanitation industry.
	 

Visit Site
 






Hüppe GmbH





Hüppe GmbH




	Headquartered in Germany, HÜPPE is the leading supplier of bath and shower enclosures and showering units throughout Europe. HÜPPE offers high-quality shower solutions that allow consumers to retreat and recharge their batteries. HÜPPE supports the end user in the design of their dream shower by offering multiple choices of shower enclosure and tray solutions at good/better/best value segments.

	Whether you are looking for classic, luxurious or modern and efficient, HÜPPE´s product offerings combine the design and the technology to satisfy the most demanding requirements. Products are available using a wide variety of glass and colors and customers can choose from an extensive selection of forms, finishes, decors and made-to-measure designs. This wide variety of options, along with the company’s impressive record of innovation and design excellence, has earned it a reputation as “The Shower Specialist.”

Visit Site
 







L


Liberty Hardware Manufacturing





Liberty Hardware Manufacturing




	Liberty Hardware Manufacturing is one of the industry’s leading manufacturers of high-quality decorative and functional hardware solutions, and decorative accessories for the home. Its products are sold through fine retail outlets, internet retailers, wholesalers and original equipment manufacturer (OEM) distribution channels. 

	Liberty’s product lines of bath hardware, bath safety, decorative cabinet, functional cabinet, builder hardware, hooks, hook rails and wall plates are available under the Liberty, Delta and Franklin Brass brands.  Liberty Hardware Manufacturing is fully committed to maintaining our leadership position through brands that exceed consumer expectations and services that meet our customers’ needs.

Visit Site
 







M


Masco Cabinetry





Masco Cabinetry




	Based in Ann Arbor, Mich., Masco Cabinetry manufactures three nationally recognized cabinetry brands, KraftMaid®, Merillat® and QualityCabinets™, and the DeNova® countertop brand. Offering an unmatched selection of stylish, high-quality products at a variety of price levels, Masco Cabinetry brands are favored by builders, dealers, distributors and home centers throughout North America. A leader in environmental stewardship, Masco Cabinetry is ISO 14001 certified in environmental management and has been granted an Environmental Stewardship Program certificate by the Kitchen Cabinet Manufacturers Association.

Visit Site
 






Masco Canada





Masco Canada




	Representing companies and brands with over 100 years of experience in the Canadian marketplace, Masco Canada brings relevant solutions for plumbing and plumbing-related goods to their business partners and consumers.  Responsible for manufacturing, product management, product development, sales and marketing, Masco Canada meets the needs of a uniquely Canadian marketplace. With manufacturing and distribution facilities based in St. Thomas, Ontario, Masco Canada represents numerous brands including Delta®, BrassCraft®, Brizo®, Delta® Commercial, Hansgrohe® and more.

Visit Site
 






Masco UK Window Group





Masco UK Window Group




	Located in the United Kingdom, Masco UK Window Group, Limited provides the complete solution for specifiers, fabricators and installers in PVC products for all market sectors. A vertically integrated business which controls full product specification from R&D, through extrusion, frame and glass manufacture to new build specification and distribution to our network of fabricators and installers.

Visit Site
 






Masterchem Industries





Masterchem Industries




	Established more than 40 years ago, Masterchem Industries LLC is a national leader in the manufacture of architectural coatings, including primers, professional and one-coat paints, spray paints, rust-preventive coatings and more. The company markets primers and specialty paints under the KILZ® brand, professional paints under the KILZ Pro-X™ brand, one-coat paints under the KILZ® Casual Colors® brand and rust-preventive coatings under the Hammerite® Rust Cap® name. These products are sold on a nationwide basis to thousands of outlets, including big box stores, national retailers, paint and hardware stores and distributors.  

Visit Site
 






Milgard Windows & Doors





Milgard Windows & Doors




	Milgard Windows & Doors is one of the largest and most trusted names in windows and doors, and is the number one considered and purchased window brand in the western United States. Whether you're doing a full home remodel, new construction, or looking for replacement windows or replacement doors, Milgard has windows and doors in shapes and styles that can be used in combinations to improve the beauty, comfort and energy efficiency of your home.

Visit Site
 






Mirolin Industries





Mirolin Industries




	Toronto-based Mirolin Industries has over 35 years of bath industry experience and knowledge and has evolved and grown to become a Canadian bath industry leader.  The Mirolin® brand is recognized in the bath industry as a leader in acrylic bath and shower products and has a solid reputation for enduring quality, design and comfort through an extensive and complete product assortment.  Their one-piece and multi-piece designs offer a bathing fixture solution to meet any home renovation or new construction application.

Visit Site
 






Moores Furniture Group





Moores Furniture Group




	West Yorkshire-based Moores Furniture Group is one of the leading manufacturers and installers of quality cabinets in the United Kingdom. The company’s product portfolio encompasses an extensive range of cabinets for the kitchen and bathroom. These are available in traditional, classical and contemporary designs as well as modern and continental styles. Moores is a market leader in the supply of cabinets to private and public sector developments as well as retail customers.

Visit Site
 







V


Vapor Technologies





Vapor Technologies




	Vapor Technologies leads its industry in the science, development and application of Physical Vapor Deposition (PVD) technologies, coatings and equipment.  Vapor Tech helped pioneer and commercialize the use of durable, decorative PVD coatings with its industry-standard Brilliance® finishes.  Today, the company manufactures advanced coating systems that are environmentally friendly and designed to meet high volume production demands.  Vapor Tech supplies its products and technology to manufacturers in a wide range of industries including consumer products, medical devices, automotive and aerospace.

Visit Site
 







W


Watkins Wellness





Watkins Wellness




	Established in 1977 in Vista, Calif., Watkins Wellness is dedicated to promoting wellness to consumers who live active lifestyles and are health conscious. The company manufactures the Endless Pools® line of aquatic fitness products, and is also the world's largest manufacturer of hot tubs, including Hot Spring® Spas, Hot Spot® Spas, Caldera® Spas, and the American Hydrotherapy Systems spa brands. With a dealer network that extends into all 50 states and more than 70 countries, Watkins Wellness is committed to helping customers around the world “Feel Good. Live Well.™”

Visit Site
 









 

 



 




