EPS for Masco Corp (MAS) Expected At $0.60


					

						July 20, 2017 - By Vivian Currie


Investors sentiment decreased to 0.76 in Q4 2016. Its down 0.05, from 0.81 in 2016Q3. It turned negative, as 67 investors sold Masco Corp shares while 216 reduced holdings. 57 funds opened positions while 158 raised stakes. 281.50 million shares or 1.49% less from 285.76 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported.
 Amer International Grp invested in 0.02% or 130,969 shares. Minnesota-based Ameriprise has invested 0.03% in Masco Corp (NYSE:MAS). Yorktown Management Rech invested in 9,200 shares. Macquarie Group Inc Ltd reported 0% stake. Dubuque Commercial Bank & holds 0% or 172 shares. Pictet Asset Ltd reported 0.29% of its portfolio in Masco Corp (NYSE:MAS). Tarbox has invested 0% of its portfolio in Masco Corp (NYSE:MAS). Fragasso Inc, Pennsylvania-based fund reported 37,614 shares. Parametric Port Assocs Limited Co reported 771,743 shares. Bancorporation Of Montreal Can invested in 0.01% or 178,216 shares. Bluecrest Cap Management invested in 162,198 shares. Capstone Asset Mngmt holds 33,993 shares or 0.03% of its portfolio. Sei Invs reported 111,011 shares. Archford Cap Strategies Lc invested in 104 shares. Renaissance Technologies Ltd Liability invested in 894,500 shares or 0.04% of the stock.

Since February 23, 2017, it had 0 buys, and 9 sales for $6.32 million activity. 1,949 shares were sold by PAYNE LISA A, worth $66,060. Another trade for 2,084 shares valued at $71,986 was made by LOSH J MICHAEL on Monday, March 20. On Thursday, June 15 Straber Renee sold $171,774 worth of Masco Corp (NYSE:MAS) or 4,452 shares. The insider Kastner Christopher K. sold $184,628. MANOOGIAN RICHARD A sold $2.24M worth of stock. VAN LOKEREN MARY ANN sold $142,317 worth of Masco Corp (NYSE:MAS) on Thursday, May 4.






Analysts await Masco Corp (NYSE:MAS) to report earnings on July, 27 before the open. They expect $0.60 EPS, up 30.43 % or $0.14 from last year’s $0.46 per share. MAS’s profit will be $193.83M for 15.93 P/E if the $0.60 EPS becomes a reality. After $0.41 actual EPS reported by Masco Corp for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts 46.34 % EPS growth. About 1.85M shares traded. Masco Corp (NYSE:MAS) has risen 18.02% since July 20, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 1.32% the S&P500.
Masco Corp (NYSE:MAS) Ratings Coverage
Among 18 analysts covering Masco (NYSE:MAS), 15 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 3 Hold. Therefore 83% are positive. Masco had 30 analyst reports since July 28, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The rating was maintained by Macquarie Research on Friday, December 16 with “Outperform”. The company was maintained on Monday, July 17 by RBC Capital Markets. The stock has “Buy” rating by Jefferies on Wednesday, May 31. Goldman Sachs initiated the stock with “Buy” rating in Tuesday, October 6 report. The company was upgraded on Wednesday, January 6 by Macquarie Research. The firm earned “Neutral” rating on Tuesday, July 28 by M Partners. The stock of Masco Corp (NYSE:MAS) has “Outperform” rating given on Wednesday, April 26 by RBC Capital Markets. On Thursday, April 7 the stock rating was maintained by Barclays Capital with “Overweight”. Barclays Capital initiated the stock with “Overweight” rating in Friday, January 6 report. The rating was initiated by Wells Fargo on Thursday, September 29 with “Outperform”.
Masco Corporation designs, manufactures, markets and distributes branded home improvement and building products. The company has market cap of $12.35 billion. The Firm operates through four business divisions: Plumbing Products, Decorative Architectural Products, Cabinetry Products, and Windows and Other Specialty Products. It has a 24.18 P/E ratio. The Company’s portfolio of brands includes BEHR paint; DELTA and HANSGROHE faucets, bath and shower fixtures; KRAFTMAID and MERILLAT cabinets; MILGARD windows and doors, and HOT SPRING spas.
